I had a pretty sad experience here recently. This is my favourite bar in my area and come often. I brought my parents here--New Yorkers of 25 years, originally from Spain. The bartender treated us in a pretty insolent way from the get-go; we were unsure why, but forgot about it. It culminated in her pre-filling out the tip line on our check with her pen. I've never experienced this, neither had my parents, and being from New York, I know it's not a thing. My father was shocked, and when he asked her why she had done this, she brushed him off and turned around. As we walked out, he told her how unfortunate he thought that had been, to which she told us to get out. This treatment was undeserved, and I don't think I'll return here, unfortunately.
